    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-07-13T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-07-13T03:00:00-05:00" n="496"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d496">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/7–1349: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister-Counselor of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Clark</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Canton</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-07-13T16:00:00+08:00"
                            >July 13, 1949—4 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received July 13—9:29 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Cantel 729. Hollington Tong,<note n="5" xml:id="d496fn5">Director of the
                        information department of the Kuomintang leadership office.</note> who
                    insists he did not come Canton in connection Gimo<note n="6" xml:id="d496fn6"
                        >Generalissimo Chiang Kai-shek.</note> visit, tells me purpose Gimo’s coming
                    here is try iron out differences which have arisen among various leaders Kmt and
                    those between himself and Li Tsung-jen. Tong says Gimo hopes persuade Li remain
                    President and that he, Gimo, will give Li full support in that office.
                    Nevertheless as head Kmt and as “revolutionary leader” Gimo feels he has certain
                    responsibilities to rally support for continued resistance Commie advance.
                    Therefore, after completing business Canton, Gimo plans visit Chungking, Chengtu
                    and possibly Lanchow. Tong says there are many differences among leaders those
                    areas which Gimo hopes to remove. He anticipates Gimo will then return Taiwan to
                    “retirement”.</p>
                <p>Sent Department Cantel 729, repeated Nanking 485, Shanghai 418.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Clark</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
